              v1.0 by B. de Magnienville, N. Creton & B. Karolewski


The purpose of this project was to build a simple shell in the C or C++ programming languages.


**************
Requirements :
	Distribution used : Linux Mint 17.2
	Compiler version : gcc 4.8.4

**************
Installation :
	In your folder, you should have 3 files : sh.cpp, a makefile and this README.
	So, type "make" and execute the script by typing "./sh".
	Congratulations ! You can now enjoy the great features of BombShell !

**************
Functionnalities :
	- Execution of basic commands like "cd", "ls", "touch" or "mkdir".
	- Execution of commands as foreground or background process groups. For example, "ls -l", "./myprog&", etc.
	- Redirection of commands standard input and standard output. For example, " echo "hello" > x.txt ", "sort < in.txt", "ls -l > myfile", etc.
	- Cascade pipelines commands such as "ls | sort | uniq | wc".
	- Send SIGHUP, SIGINT (CTRL+C), and SIGQUIT (CTRL+\) signals to the right process groups.
	- List background processes with the command "listbg".
	- Exit BomberShell by typing "exit" (whick kills all the processes) or press "CTRL+D".

